            <h2>How Did the Dinosaurs Die Out?</h2>
            <p>
                <i>Scientists think that dinosaurs died out because Earth got too cold and there wasn’t any food. But they aren’t sure what caused this.</i>
            </p>
            <p>
                <i>A meteorite hit Earth in Chicxulub in Mexico and some scientists think this is the reason. Others believe that a very big volcano in India erupted and made problems for the dinosaurs. Meteorites and volcanoes create clouds of dust.</i>
            </p>
            <p>
                <i>This dust blocked the Sun. It was winter for a long time and food didn’t grow. Other scientists think that the weather changed on Earth over a long time – it got slowly colder and colder until the dinosaurs couldn’t survive.</i>
            </p>
        </block>
